The malfunction of the temperature gauge can lead to engine overheating, causing engine damage, cracking of the engine block or head, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the defrost system can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
The smell of gasoline can indicate a fuel leak, which can cause fires or explosions, leading to accidents or injuries.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly

reaching high speeds without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, personal injury, or even death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning front seat belt latch can lead to accidents or injuries due to the belt coming unlatched while driving, compromising the safety of the driver and passengers.

the seat belt latch comes undone by itself while driving
uncertainty about the reliability of the seat belt in the event of an accident.

symptoms: and MPG gauge stop working or are not displaying accurate readings
the instrument cluster is not functioning properly.
